{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This family of proteins includes Krev interaction trapped protein 1 (KRIT1), its paralogue FERM domain-containing protein 8 (FRMD8) and closely related proteins. Members of this entry are involved in various cellular processes, including the stabilisation of cell surface proteins, regulation of signaling pathways, and maintenance of cellular homeostasis.</p>\n\n<p>FRMD8 promotes the stability of iRhom1/RHBDF1 and iRhom2/RHBDF2, preventing their degradation and facilitating ADAM17-mediated shedding of ligands such as TNF and growth factors [[cite:PUB00154949], [cite:PUB00154950]]. They also play a role in negatively regulating Wnt signaling [[cite:PUB00154946]].</p>\n\n<p>KRIT1 is part of the CCM signaling pathway, crucial for cardiovascular development, acting as negative regulators of angiogenesis and influencing endothelial cell functions [[cite:PUB00154947]] [[cite:PUB00154948]]. They interact with integrins and participate in maintaining intracellular reactive oxygen species homeostasis, which is essential for preventing oxidative damage and modulating cell proliferation [[cite:PUB00076169], [[cite:PUB00103011]]. Additionally, they are involved in the regulation of macroautophagy and cellular polarity through interactions with various proteins and signaling cascades [[cite:PUB00154948]]. Mutations in this proteins are related to cerebral cavernous malformations.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "4hdo", "name" "Crystal structure of the binary Complex of KRIT1 bound to the Rap1 GTPase"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR043058", "name" "KRIT, N-terminal NPxY motif-rich domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR13283" "KREV INTERACTION TRAPPED 1-RELATED"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "KRIT1/FRMD8", "short" "KRIT1/FRMD8"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :cou